Imagery Description: Eros with fillet and alabastron flying above nude woman, with 'melonNon Sepcifiedslice' hair, and outstretched arms; to left, folded drapery above cista. Part of a wing in the outer border. Looks to go closely with Paestum 48432; cf. also the vases from Spinazzo. Frr. E 64/65 III give part of the border, with birds, palmette, and ivy.
